datafield.subfield: Stars and stripes (Altdorf, Nürnberger Land, Germany : Southern Germany ed.)

"Daily Newspaper of U.S. Armed Forces in the European Theater of Operations," May 8, 1945-<May 21, 1945>; "Newspaper of U.S. Armed Forces in the European Theater," <Aug. 15, 1945>-Nov. 3, 1945; "Unofficial Newspaper of U.S. Armed Forces in the European Theater," Nov. 5, 1945-Apr. 17, 1946.
Official publication was preceeded by a "dry run" issue dated May 1, 1945.
Issue for Aug. 15, 1945 also published in 2nd ed. called "Victory ed."
Has suppl. published on Wednesday with title: Midweek in Central Europe, Aug. 22-Sept. 19, 1945; and: Midweek, Sept. 26, 1946-<Jan. 16, 1946>
Also available on microfilm from New York Public Library and International Microfilm Press.

Published under auspices of: Information and Education Division, ETOUSA, May 8-21, 1945; Information and Education Division, TSFET, Aug. 15, 1945-Feb. 7, 1946; Information and Education Section, USFET, Feb. 8-10, 1946; Information and Education Service, USFET, Feb. 11-Apr. 17, 1946.
Merged with: Stars and stripes (Pfungstadt, Germany : Germany ed.), to form: Stars and stripes (Altdorf, Nürnberger Land, Germany : European ed.).
